Smite Impudence			KEY:Insinuator ~ Smite Impudence		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Antipaladin Class Feature.InsinuatorClassFeatures.SpecialAttack.Supernatural																		SOURCEPAGE:p.20		DESC:%1 times per day, an insinuator can beseech the forces empowering him to punish their shared enemies. As a swift action, the insinuator chooses one target within sight to smite. An insinuator cannot use smite against a target that shares an alignment with the outsider he has invoked for the day. The insinuator adds %2 on his attack rolls and %3 on all damage rolls made against the target of his smite. If the target is an outsider, dragon, or divine spellcaster with an alignment opposed to that of the outsider he has invoked for the day, the bonus damage on the first successful attack increases to %4 points of damage. Regardless of the target, the smite attack automatically bypasses any damage reduction the creature might possess. In addition, each time the insinuator declares a smite, he gains %4 temporary hit points. The smite effect remains until the target is defeated or the next time the insinuator rests and regains his uses of this ability.|SmiteImpudenceTimes|SmiteImpudenceAttackBonus|SmiteImpudenceDamageBonus|SmiteImpudenceLVL	DEFINE:SmiteImpudenceTimes|0	DEFINE:SmiteImpudenceAttackBonus|0	DEFINE:SmiteImpudenceDamageBonus|0	DEFINE:SmiteImpudenceLVL|0	BONUS:VAR|SmiteImpudenceTimes|min((SmiteImpudenceLVL+2)/3,7)	BONUS:VAR|SmiteImpudenceAttackBonus|max(CHA,0)	BONUS:VAR|SmiteImpudenceDamageBonus|SmiteImpudenceLVL/2	BONUS:VAR|SmiteImpudenceLVL|AntipaladinLVL	ASPECT:CheckCount|%1|SmiteImpudenceTimes	ASPECT:CheckType|Uses per day
